	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-02-02T22:34:33">3i Infrastructure plc (3i Infrastructure) is a closed-ended investment company. The Company invests in infrastructure businesses and assets. The Company makes equity and junior or mezzanine debt investments. It invests in companies with stable underlying performance: asset-intensive businesses, providing essential services over the long term, often on a regulated basis, or with contracted revenues. Its objective is to provide shareholders with a total return of 12% per annum over the long term, to be achieved by building and managing a balanced portfolio of infrastructure investments. Its investments are in unquoted companies. 3i Investments plc, a wholly-owned subsidiary of 3i Group plc, acts as the investment adviser to the Company. The Company sold its 50% holding in Alpha Schools (Highland) Holdings Limited (Alpha Schools) to HICL Infrastructure Company Limited.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2016-02-08T09:49:31">BRIEF: For the six months ended 30 September 2015, 3i Infrastructure PLC revenues decreased 27% to L87.5M. Net income decreased 31% to L80.7M. Revenues reflect United Kingdom segment decrease of 79% to L28.3M. Net income also reflects Unrealised (losses)/gains on the fair va increase from L12M (income) to L4.8M (expense), Operating Expenses increase of 8% to L1.4M (expense). Dividend per share remained flat at L0.04.</Text>
